tags: Treatment satisfaction,
review: No appointment for seeing patients should' have  been given if treatment ( filling the decayed teeth ) couldn't be given.  Whereas fees is taken but treatment is withheld citing Covid-19 restrictions. If the doctor is aware that treatment cannot be given she could have saved us the futile visit when appointment is sought.
reply_text: Dear mam,on the telephonic conversation,we clearly asked you if there's any emergency.You said that one old filling is lost and the cavity is becoming deep and the kid is having problem.That's why we called for consultation.On examination it was found that the filling is intact and a couple of new cavities were found which require fillings.I suggested we do the fillings at a later date as we are not supposed to perform any aerosol generating procedures now keeping in mind the safety of the patient and the clinic staff as per Govt  regulations.Sorry for the inconvenience.
